title WordPress REST Search Flow\n<size:11><i>GET /wp/v2/search — WP_REST_Search_Controller (WordPress 5.0+)</i></size>

|Client|
start
:Send **GET /wp/v2/search**\n?search=…&type=…&subtype=…&page=…;

|WP_REST_Search_Controller|
:Route matched: register_routes()\nmaps GET /search → get_items();

note right
  permission_callback =
  get_items_permission_check()
end note

:**get_items_permission_check**($request);

note right
  Always returns **true**
  Search endpoint is public —
  no authentication required
end note

:Proceed to parameter sanitization;

:**sanitize_subtypes**($subtypes, $request, $parameter);
:wp_parse_slug_list($subtypes)\n— normalize input to array of slugs;
:rest_parse_request_arg($subtypes, $request, $parameter)\n— validate each slug against registered enum;

if (Validation failed?) then (yes)
    :Return **WP_Error**\n(invalid subtype values);
    |Client|
    :Receive **400 Bad Request**;
    stop
else (no)
endif

|WP_REST_Search_Controller|
if ('any' present in subtypes?) then (yes)
    :Collapse subtypes → **['any']**\n(overrides all other subtype filters);
else (no)
    :Resolve handler to filter valid subtypes;
    :**get_search_handler**($request)\n— resolve handler by type param;

    if (Type missing or not registered?) then (yes)
        :Return **WP_Error**\n'rest_search_invalid_type' 400;
        |Client|
        :Receive **400 Bad Request**;
        stop
    else (no)
    endif

    |WP_REST_Search_Controller|
    :array_intersect($subtypes, $handler->get_subtypes())\n— keep only subtypes supported by handler;
endif

:**get_items**($request) — main collection handler;
:**get_search_handler**($request)\n— look up handler by $request->get_param('type');

if (Handler lookup failed?) then (yes)
    :Return **WP_Error**\n'rest_search_invalid_type' 400;
    |Client|
    :Receive **400 Bad Request**;
    stop
else (no)
endif

|WP_REST_Search_Handler|
:**search_items**(WP_REST_Request $request)\n— delegate DB query to concrete handler subclass;
note right
  Returns: ['ids' => [...], 'total' => N]
  RESULT_IDS + RESULT_TOTAL constants
end note
:Return search result array;

|WP_REST_Search_Controller|
if (Result missing 'ids' or 'total' keys?) then (yes)
    :Return **WP_Error**\n'rest_search_handler_error' 500;
    |Client|
    :Receive **500 Internal Server Error**;
    stop
else (no)
endif

|WP_REST_Search_Controller|
:array_map('absint', $result['ids'])\n— cast all IDs to positive integers;
:Calculate pagination:\n$total, $page, $per_page\n$max_pages = ceil($total / $per_page);

if ($page > $max_pages AND $total > 0?) then (yes)
    :Return **WP_Error**\n'rest_search_invalid_page_number' 400;
    |Client|
    :Receive **400 Bad Request**;
    stop
else (no)
endif

|WP_REST_Search_Controller|
:Loop over $ids\n→ prepare_item_for_response($id, $request);

note right
  For each item:
  • get_search_handler() called again per item
  • get_fields_for_response() — determine included fields
  • handler->prepare_item($id, $fields) — fetch item data
  • add_additional_fields_to_object() — registered field extensions
  • filter_response_by_context($data, 'view'|'embed') — strip out-of-context fields
  • handler->prepare_item_links($id) — HAL links (abstract)
  • Append 'collection' link → rest_url('wp/v2/search')
  • response->add_links($links)
end note

fork
    |WP_REST_Search_Handler|
    :**prepare_item**($id, $fields)\n— concrete subclass fetches item data;
    :Return item data array;
fork again
    |WP_REST_Search_Handler|
    :**prepare_item_links**($id)\n— concrete subclass returns HAL links;
    :Return links array;
end fork

|WP_REST_Search_Controller|
:Collect prepared items\ninto $results array;

:rest_ensure_response($results)\n— wrap in WP_REST_Response;

:Set response headers:\n**X-WP-Total**: $total\n**X-WP-TotalPages**: $max_pages;

if ($page > 1?) then (yes)
    :Add **Link: prev** header;
else (no)
endif

if ($page < $max_pages?) then (yes)
    :Add **Link: next** header;
else (no)
endif

:Return **WP_REST_Response**\n(paginated collection with HAL links);

|Client|
:Receive **200 OK**\nJSON array of search results\n+ pagination headers;
stop

@enduml
